==English==

===Noun===
'''brand linkage'''  (''plural:'' '''brand linkages''')

# (Advertising) the degree to which the consumer understands a commercial’s message is for a specific [[brand]] of product rather than the product category.
#:''* If viewers remember a funny commercial was for tissues instead of the brand Puffs, then the ad has poor '''brand linkage.'''


